            If Ancelotti opts for a midfield trio of Modric, Lucas Silva and Isco, it will be the sixteenth different combination Ancelotti has chosen this season. Of the other 15, the most successful in the 4-3-3 is Modric-Kroos-James (seven wins in seven matches), while the worst was the trio formed of Sami Khedira, Kroos and Isco (with those three in the starting line-up, Madrid lost 4-0 at the Caldern and 4-3 against Schalke). In a 4-4-2 system, the most used midfield configuration consisted of Kroos, Modric, James and Isco (five wins and just one defeat).
